{
  "title": "VIP Programmable Spacefighters",
  "author": "RCA COSMAC VIP Game Manual, 1978",
  "description": "Program 2-8 ships, then execute combat rounds with movement and fire commands.",
  "sidebar": [
    "## How To Play",
    "1. Enter game parameters:",
    "   S=spacefighters (1-8), D=defense (1-F),",
    "   E=entries (1-F), C=clock (0-F),",
    "   F=fire power (1-F), A=accum (0-F).",
    "2. Check fighter defense/position (0 to exit).",
    "3. Program each surviving fighter in order.",
    "4. Enter 0 to start command execution.",
    "5. Enter 0 again after a round to continue.",
    "",
    "## Programming Commands",
    "0 = Rest; begin next fighter",
    "1 = Rotate 45 deg CCW + move",
    "2 = Move forward",
    "3 = Rotate 45 deg CW + move",
    "4 = Rotate 45 deg CCW",
    "5 = Fire",
    "6 = Rotate 45 deg CW",
    "8 = Erase all and reprogram fighter",
    "E = End current fighter programming",
    "7,9,A,C,D,F = Rest / no-op",
    "",
    "## Parameter Meanings",
    "A (accum): unused fire power carries",
    "forward when 1-F; 0 disables carryover.",
    "C (clock): setup timer per fighter.",
    "0=off, 1-F=phorseks (4 sec each).",
    "D (defense): starting defense points",
    "for each fighter (1-F).",
    "E (entries): commands each fighter can",
    "program per round (1-F).",
    "F (fire power): shots available per",
    "round before accumulation effects.",
    "S (spacefighters): number of fighters (1-8)."
  ]
}
